title: Pilot
description: Blossom hears her parents arguing, they tell Blossom they have an appointment with a lawyer. Blossom dreams about what it will be like if her parents divorce.

title: Blossom Blossoms
description: Blossom reaches puberty and substitutes an older friend for her absentee mother to talk about it.

title: Dad's Girlfriend
description: Blossom has problems with her dad's new girlfriend.

title: Who's in Charge Here?
description: When Blossom is in charge of the home for one night, when her father performs on a cruise ship, she sees Anthony's new girlfriend stealing a family heirloom.

title: Sex, Lies and Teenagers
description: Blossom sneaks off to a make-out party.

title: I Ain't Got No Buddy
description: Blossom feels left out when Six befriends a chic new student; the kids keep Nick from seeing his divorce papers.

title: Thanks for the Memorex
description: Inspired by old home movies Blossom transferred to video, the family goes to the cabin by the lake.

title: The Geek
description: When she gets tricked to go to the homecoming dance with a school geek, Blossom blames herself. Joey wants to get his driver's license

title: Tough Love
description: Nick challenges Tony to get a job or move out. Tony gets a job, but gets fired, so Nick makes him move out of the class. Meanwhile, Blossom tries to write a song for a music class.

title: Papa's Little Dividend
description: A woman whom Nick had a fling with shows up claiming that he is the father of her child.

title: Three O'Clock and All Is Hell
All Hallows Eve
description: On Halloween, Blossom and Six fight off a masked maniac: Joey, who is trying to sneak in after going to a party grounded. Meanwhile, Nick, Anthony and Buzz dress up as Wilson Phillips to win a cash prize, but get stranded at a bar.

title: Losing Your... Religion
description: As part of a Social Studies mid-term, Blossom becomes Jewish for a week. In the meantime, she becomes concerned when Six tells her she is planning to lose her virginity to a guy from school.

title: The Best Laid Plans of Mice and Men
Six and Sonny
description: Six gets into a relationship with a married ex-convict who is ten years older than her. Meanwhile, Joey writes a letter to the president.

title: Blossom's Dilemma
description: When Six runs off with Sonny, Blossom is conflicted as to whether she should tell where they are.

title: 38 Special
description: Blossom discovers that a schoolmate keeps a gun in his locker and Joey comes across an alcoholic clown.

title: A Little Help from My Friends
A Kiss Is Just a Kiss
A Mind with a Heart of Its Own
The Date
description: Blossom looks forward to her first prom date, with Joey's friend Bobby, but after Joey warns him about Bobby's reputation as a ladies' man, Nick forbids her to go out with him.

title: So Many Milestones, So Little Time
